# Todo:
**Purpose:** Tool to produce social media voice caption/visualization


## Current Task: (0.6.0)
**Goal:** Integrate my existing Local SRT and Caption Animator projects into this project, and so create a single
one-stop-shop for my YT Video/Short production process.

**Work flow:**
- Creating YT video:
  - Record and edit audio
  - Create visualizer using Audio Visualizer
  - Use DaVinci Resolve to overlay visualizer over fixed background image
- Creating Short video:
  - Record and edit auido
  - Generate SRT
  - Edit SRT
  - Generate Caption video from SRT
  - User DaVinci Resolve to overlay caption with adio over fixed background image

Both work flows should be integrated into this single app.

### Stage One: (COMPLETED)
- Review all the files in `.agents/*` and update them to properly align with the projec code in `src/*`. IGNORE ALL FILES IN `Projects to integrate/`.

### Stage Two: (COMPLETED)
- There are two projects in `Projects to integrate/`;
  - Caption Animator (`Projects to integrate/Caption Animator/`)
  - Local SRT (`Projects to integrate/Local SRT/`)
- Each project I am currently implementing on its own. The goal is to merge each project into this project.
- At the end of the merge:
  - Local SRT will simply be a `srt` package in the `audio_visualizer` package
  - Caption Animator will simply be a `caption` package in the `audio_visualizer` package
  - The CLI interface for both Caption Animator and Local SRT will no longer exist, they will
    exist purely as internal packages for the Audio Visualizer project to use.

### Stage Three:
- The existing GUI need to be adjusted to use a main tab layout, where there is tab for the following screens:
  - Audio Visualizer (default): This is the current main screen
  - SRT Gen: Screen to select audio files and then generate SRT file using the `audio_visualizer.srt` package.
    This screen should allow the user to set the different settings for the srt gen.
  - SRT Edit: Screen to allow the user to view a waveform and the srt timestamps, and then adjust the timestamps.
  - Caption Animate: Screen to select srt files and then generate video files using the `audio_visualizer.caption` package.
    This screen should allow the user to set the different settings for the caption generation.
  - Render Composition: Screen to allow the user to load a background video/image, audio, and results from the other
    tabs (for example Audio Visualizer, and Caption Animate) and then layout the different elements and render into
    a single video file.


## v0.7.0
### Edit SRT Screen
- Load SRT bundle produced by SRT Gen screen to work on word-level parings
- Timeline segment boarders need to expand width when highlighted to make it easier for the the to click and drag
- Selecting a transcription row should not zoom in on the timeline to the segment, but should pan/scroll the timeline
  to the cooresponding segment
- Split segment at playhead on timeline by right click menu.
- Split segment should split at playhead location if within the segment
- Ability to drag and select a section on timeline to create new segment
- Adding new segments should auto resort table by time start

### Render Composition Screen
- Ability to set audio volume
- Ability to "scrub" the timeline and update the live preview
- Live preview should auto update when ever the user places the track head on the timeline
- User should be able to stop `[]`/start `|>`/jump to start `<<`/jump to end `>>` using the
  standard symbols for the functions in the live preview panel. User should be able to press
  space to start/stop live preview playback.
- Audio tracks on timeline should have basic waveform that can be generated more quickly than in SRT Edit.
- Video/Graphic tracks should be stacked in accending Z order upwards on the timeline while audio tracks should
  be stacked in ascending order downwards:
  '''
  video at z=2
  video at z=1
  audio at z=1
  audio at z=2
  ```
- When a video asset with audio is added, both video and audio should be added to the timeline. User should then
  be able to remove just the audio or video track from the timeline.
- Visual asserts should have a button to resize to original and resize to output size
- Video Position & Size label/input boxes have big gap between instead of being next to each other
- Video Size ratio (w & h) should be locked so when one is change they all adjust

### SRT Gen Screen
- The user should be able to pass in the plain text of a script for a particular audio file and this is used to
  help automatically generate/correct the srt file.
- Ability to see downloaded models and delete downloaded models.
- Investigate how hard it would be to refine/training existing model for the users voice.

### Visualizers
- Set video dimensions by number of objects in visualizer
- Future visualizers:
    - Cloud/Particles
    - Ring

### Caption Animator:
- Improved animation support:
  - Add ability to set font bold or italics
  - Add ability to configure margins and paddings in interactive
  - Add ability to merge audio with captions
  - Create animation like word_reveal called word highlight where words are highlighted one by one
  - Create a new animation that mimics a typewriter effect
  - Add ability to highlight specific words in a sentence
  - For many of the abilities, take in a general srt and word-level srt to produce the proper effect.
- Render should not produce an `*_caption.mp4` file and `*_caption_overlay.mov` but a single `*_caption.mp4`

### SRT:
- Improve test benchmarking harness to be configurable to point at folder with .mp3 and .srt and a set of
  setting configurations and then run these configurations on the inputs and generate results based upon
  outputs compared to provided srt.

### Future Features
- Video-linked SRT editing:
  - Add real video preview alongside waveform editing
  - Support frame stepping, in/out point setting from playhead, and subtitle-in-context preview
- Speaker-aware styling:
  - Map diarized speakers to caption styles, colors, positions, or animation presets
- Template / brand kit system:
  - Save reusable fonts, colors, logos, lower-thirds, caption styles, composition layouts, and export targets
- Deliverable bundles:
  - Export final MP4, transparent caption overlay, sidecar SRT/VTT, transcript outputs, and platform-specific variants in one pass
- Review / approval mode:
  - Add issue markers, revision notes, autosave history, restore points, and side-by-side subtitle diffs
- Batch queue + watch folders:
  - Queue multiple end-to-end jobs and optionally trigger workflows from watched asset folders
- Multilingual / localization workflow:
  - Support multiple subtitle tracks, shared timing across languages, and multi-language export bundles
- Context-aware cleanup:
  - Add smarter transcript cleanup for names, punctuation, speaker labels, and subtitle text consistency
